.TH "Screen.width" "JS" "April 8, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Screen.width \- Screen: width property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Screen.width\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property returns the
width of the screen in CSS pixels.
.SH VALUE
A number.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// Crude way to check that the screen is at least 1024x768\f[R]
\f[B]if\f[R] (window.screen.width >= 1024 && window.screen.height >= 768) {
  \f[I]// Resolution is 1024x768 or above\f[R]
}
.EE
.SH NOTES
Note that not all of the width given by this property may be available
to the window itself.
When other widgets occupy space that cannot be used by the
\f[CR]window\f[R] object, there is a difference in
\f[CR]window.screen.width\f[R] and \f[CR]window.screen.availWidth\f[R].
See also \f[CR]screen.height\f[R].
